&amp;section=3D20" title=3D"Edit section: Many explanatory variables, two c=
ategories"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</s=
pan></span></div>
<p>The above example of binary logistic regression on one explanatory varia=
ble can be generalized to binary logistic regression on any number of expla=
natory variables <i>x<sub>1</sub>, x<sub>2</sub>,...</i> and any number of =
categorical values <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"=
><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"displ=
ay: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\=
displaystyle y=3D0,1,2,\dots }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>y</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mn>0</mn>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mn>2</mn>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mo>=E2=80=A6<!-- =E2=80=A6 --></mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle y=3D0,1,2,\do=
ts }</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/5e6fdd26982492d75ac168027bcd44c43151049c" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:13.566ex; height:2.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle y=
=3D0,1,2,\dots }"></span>.
</p><p>To begin with, we may consider a logistic model with <i>M</i> explan=
atory variables, <i>x<sub>1</sub></i>, <i>x<sub>2</sub></i> ... <i>x<sub>M<=
/sub></i> and, as in the example above, two categorical values (<i>y</i> =
=3D 0 and 1). For the simple binary logistic regression model, we assumed a=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linear_model" title=3D"Linear mod=
el">linear relationship</a> between the predictor variable and the log-odds=
 (also called <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logit" title=3D"Logi=
t">logit</a>) of the event that <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-el=
ement-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" s=
tyle=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" =
alttext=3D"{\displaystyle y=3D1}">
