-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:2.115ex; height:2.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \be=
ta _{i}}"></span> are parameters of the model. An additional generalization=
 has been introduced in which the base of the model (<i>b</i>) is not restr=
icted to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euler%27s_number" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Euler's number">Euler's number</a> <i>e</i>. In m=
ost applications, the base <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element=
-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=
=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" altt=
ext=3D"{\displaystyle b}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
