></span> of the logarithm is usually taken to be <i><a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/E_(mathematical_constant)" title=3D"E (mathematical const=
ant)">e</a></i>. However, in some cases it can be easier to communicate res=
ults by working in base 2 or base 10.
</p><p>For a more compact notation, we will specify the explanatory variabl=
es and the <i>=CE=B2</i> coefficients as <span class=3D"nowrap">=E2=81=A0<s=
pan class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-m=
ath-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmln=
