<p>This functional form is commonly called a single-layer <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Perceptron" title=3D"Perceptron">perceptron</a> or =
single-layer <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artificial_neural_net=
work" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Artificial neural network">artificial =
neural network</a>. A single-layer neural network computes a continuous out=
put instead of a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Step_function" ti=
tle=3D"Step function">step function</a>. The derivative of <i>p<sub>i</sub>=
</i> with respect to  <i>X</i>&nbsp;=3D&nbsp;(<i>x</i><sub>1</sub>, ..., <i=
>x</i><sub><i>k</i></sub>) is computed from the general form:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
