<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"In_terms_of_binomial_data">=
In terms of binomial data</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D=
"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/inde=
x.php?title=3DLogistic_regression&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D29" title=
=3D"Edit section: In terms of binomial data"><span>edit</span></a><span cla=
ss=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>A closely related model assumes that each <i>i</i> is associated not wit=
h a single Bernoulli trial but with <i>n</i><sub><i>i</i></sub> <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Independent_identically_distributed" class=3D=
"mw-redirect" title=3D"Independent identically distributed">independent ide=
ntically distributed</a> trials, where the observation <i>Y</i><sub><i>i</i=
></sub> is the number of successes observed (the sum of the individual Bern=
oulli-distributed random variables), and hence follows a <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binomial_distribution" title=3D"Binomial distributio=
n">binomial distribution</a>:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e Y_{i}\,\sim \operatorname {Bin} (n_{i},p_{i}),{\text{ for }}i=3D1,\dots ,=
n}">
