</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Pseudo-R-squared">Pseudo-R-=
squared</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-br=
acket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DLogi=
stic_regression&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D39" title=3D"Edit section: =
Pseudo-R-squared"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracke=
t">]</span></span></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pseudo-R-squared" ti=
tle=3D"Pseudo-R-squared">Pseudo-R-squared</a></div>
<p>In linear regression the squared multiple correlation, <span class=3D"te=
xhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">R</span><sup>2</sup> is used to as=
sess goodness of fit as it represents the proportion of variance in the cri=
terion that is explained by the predictors.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Cohen_35-4" =
class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logistic_regre=
ssion#cite_note-Cohen-35"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>35<span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> In logistic regression analysis, ther=
e is no agreed upon analogous measure, but there are several competing meas=
ures each with limitations.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Cohen_35-5" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logistic_regression#cite_note-=
Cohen-35"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>35<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-:0_36-0" class=3D"reference"><a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logistic_regression#cite_note-:0-36"><s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>36<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span><=
/a></sup>
</p><p>Four of the most commonly used indices and one less commonly used on=
e are examined on this page:
</p>
<ul><li>Likelihood ratio <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:i=
talic;">R</span><sup>2</sup><sub>L</sub></li>
<li>Cox and Snell <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;"=
>R</span><sup>2</sup><sub>CS</sub></li>
<li>Nagelkerke <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">R<=
/span><sup>2</sup><sub>N</sub></li>
<li>McFadden <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">R</s=
pan><sup>2</sup><sub>McF</sub></li>
<li>Tjur <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">R</span>=
<sup>2</sup><sub>T</sub></li></ul>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Hosmer=E2=80=93Lemeshow_tes=
t"><span id=3D"Hosmer.E2.80.93Lemeshow_test"></span>Hosmer=E2=80=93Lemeshow=
 test</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brac=
ket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DLogist=
ic_regression&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D40" title=3D"Edit section: Ho=
smer=E2=80=93Lemeshow test"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsect=
ion-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hosmer%E2%80%93Lemeshow_tes=
t" title=3D"Hosmer=E2=80=93Lemeshow test">Hosmer=E2=80=93Lemeshow test</a> =
uses a test statistic that asymptotically follows a <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Chi-squared_distribution" title=3D"Chi-squared distributi=
on"><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D=
"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><mat=
h xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle \c=
hi ^{2}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
