nt rates match expected event rates in subgroups of the model population.  =
This test is considered to be obsolete by some statisticians because of its=
 dependence on arbitrary binning of predicted probabilities and relative lo=
w power.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-37" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.w=
